[[File:Gold ore detail.png|left|120px]]
'''Gold ore''' can be mined at level 40 [[Mining]] providing 65 Mining experience. After a [[gold rock]] is mined, it will take 60 seconds until it reappears. Gold ore is used to smelt [[gold bar|gold bars]]. Smelting a gold bar gives 22.5 [[Smithing]] experience, or 56.2 with the [[goldsmith gauntlets]] equipped. The bar can then be crafted into various types of [[jewellery]] through the [[Crafting]] skill at a furnace, rather than an anvil like other bars. An anvil is used however to make a [[gold helmet]] or [[golden bowl]] for the quests [[Between a Rock...]] and [[Legends' Quest]]. Many items require a [[mould]] to create.

The chance to successfully mine gold ore scales linearly with the player's mining level. Were it possible to mine gold ore at level 1, players would have a 3% chance per mining cycle to successfully mine the ore. At level 99, players have a 29% chance to successfully mine the ore per mining cycle.{{CiteTwitter|author=Mod Ash|url=https://twitter.com/JagexAsh/status/1269272117176041472|date=6 June 2020|archiveurl=https://archive.is/bGU9S|archivedate=6 June 2020}}

Wearing either [[mining gloves]] or [[expert mining gloves]] while mining a gold rock grants a 33.33% chance for the rock to not deplete upon mining a gold ore, allowing the player to mine an additional ore before depleting.

